The paper deals with compressed sensing and signal processing, which are both covered by the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) sub-categories. The use of fusion frames is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also mentions numerical examples, which could indicate that it falls under the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses robustness to noise, which could make it relevant to the cs.SI (Systems and Control) sub-category.
